+---
+name: agent-planning-workflow
+description: Runs the suggestion-first planning workflow from a rough project idea to a reviewable planning package in Linear. Use when the user asks to "plan a project", "turn this idea into a planning package", "draft planning without committing todos", "suggestion-first planning", or before implementation starts on a new initiative. Use when planner agents must not silently promote assumptions to Todo, Ready, or In Progress. Do not use for picking up verified execution work (use pickup-work) or writing a single filled document without the full workflow (use project-docs).
+---
+
+# Agent Planning Workflow
+Use this skill to take a rough idea from zero to a **human-reviewable planning package** without creating committed execution work.
+
+The full contract lives in `references/suggestion-first-planning-workflow.md`. Read it before changing Linear or drafting canonical docs.
+
+## When to use
+- New product, feature line, or repo needs planning before coding.
+- User wants Linear issues and docs drafted as **Suggestion** first.
+- Multiple project-docs templates and planner structure issues must be sequenced.
+- Replacing ad-hoc "create todos and start" agent behavior.
+
+## When not to use
+- User already verified the planning package and only wants execution → `pickup-work` or `task-spec`.
+- User wants one document only → `project-docs`.
+- User explicitly asked to create **Todo** issues immediately → confirm once, then skip to their requested state for those items only.
+
+## Workflow
+1. Read `references/suggestion-first-planning-workflow.md`.
+2. **Phase 1 — Intake:** Gather sources, assumptions, and constraints. Post an intake summary on the driving **Suggestion** issue or create one.
+3. **Phase 2 — Project placement:** Link or propose initiative/project in **Planning** with **Suggestion** issues. Do not create committed projects without user confirmation.
+4. **Phase 3 — Document plan:** Use `project-docs` placement rules and README planner guide. Output a document plan table (template, surface, phase).
+5. **Phase 4 — Route uncertainty:** Send decisions, risks, and questions to the right templates/logs. Draft decision records and seeds only as **Suggestion** / draft.
+6. **Phase 5 — Suggestion issues:** Create the planning issue set (optionally from `create-planner-project` structure) entirely in **Suggestion**. Add a planning package index issue linking brief, milestone outline, risks, and open questions.
+7. **Phase 6 — Human verification:** Stop. Present the review checklist from the reference. Update drafts from feedback only.
+8. **Phase 7 — Conversion:** Only after explicit human approval, promote issues to **Todo**/**Ready**, add implementation briefs via `task-spec`, and set first execution backlog order.
+
+## Field rules
+- Default all new planner-created issues to **Suggestion**.
+- Never assign a cycle unless the user asks.
+- Never move the project to **In Progress** during phases 1–6.
+- Link canonical docs; do not paste full duplicates into issues.
+- For document drafting, call `project-docs` with the document plan from phase 3.
+- For Linear skeletons, call `create-planner-project` but enforce **Suggestion** defaults from this workflow.
+- Record assumptions and open questions visibly; do not fold them into acceptance criteria as if settled.
+
+## Outputs checklist
+Before asking for human review, confirm the package includes:
+
+- [ ] Initiative and project links (or clear proposal)
+- [ ] Document plan aligned with placement rules
+- [ ] Project brief draft or explicit deferral with reason
+- [ ] Milestone outline (milestones or milestone plan doc)
+- [ ] Open questions log seed with blocking vs non-blocking tags
+- [ ] Risk register seed
+- [ ] Linked decision record drafts where choices were made
+- [ ] **Suggestion** issue set with planning package index
+- [ ] No **Todo** / **In Progress** issues unless user explicitly excepted them
+
