+# Suggestion-first agent planning workflow
+Contract for planner agents, planner skills, and planner entrypoints. Takes a rough project idea from zero to a **reviewable planning package** without silently turning assumptions into committed work.
+
+## Purpose
+The doc-template library (`project-docs` templates and skills) can produce strong individual documents, but agents still need one workflow that sequences intake, Linear placement, document selection, routing, and human verification before execution issues exist.
+
+This workflow is that contract. Every new planner skill and agent entrypoint should follow it unless a human explicitly opts into a faster path.
+
+## Core invariants
+1. **Suggestion before commitment.** New initiatives, projects, issues, and scope changes start in Linear **Suggestion** (or equivalent draft-only surfaces) until a human verifies them.
+2. **Documents before todos.** Planning artifacts are drafted and linked before implementation issues move to **Todo**, **Ready**, or **In Progress**.
+3. **One canonical owner per fact.** Use `documentation-placement-rules` and the project-docs chain; do not duplicate briefs, risks, or decisions across surfaces.
+4. **Visible uncertainty.** Assumptions, open questions, and unresolved risks stay labeled until a human accepts or routes them.
+5. **No silent promotion.** Agents do not move work to committed states, assign cycles, or create implementation todos without an explicit human review gate.
+
+## Linear state model
+|State|Meaning|Who may set it|
+|---|---|---|
+|**Suggestion**|Proposed scope, doc draft, or work item awaiting human triage.|Planner agents during phases 1–5.|
+|**Todo** / **Ready**|Human-verified work queued for execution.|Humans after phase 6; agents only when the user explicitly confirms promotion in the same session.|
+|**In Progress**|Active implementation or committed planning execution.|Humans or execution agents after verification.|
+|**Done** / **Canceled**|Closed outcomes.|Humans or assignees with normal Linear permissions.|
+
+**Suggestion projects:** When no real project exists yet, create or propose a Linear project in **Planning** with status and issues defaulting to **Suggestion**. Name it so it is obvious it is pre-commitment (for example `<Product> Planning (suggested)`).
+
+## Phases
+
+### Phase 1 — Intake and source/context gathering
+**Goal:** Understand the rough idea and what evidence already exists.
+
+**Inputs:** User prompt, linked Linear issues or documents, repo README, existing `documents/` or Linear docs, prior art links, constraints named by the user.
+
+**Actions:**
+
+- Capture the problem statement, audience hint, surfaces (web, native, API, automation, AI, etc.), and known constraints.
+- Inventory sources: initiative docs, project docs, repo `documents/`, research links, ADRs, related issues.
+- List assumptions separately from verified facts.
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|Notes|
+|---|---|---|
+|Intake summary|Linear comment on the driving issue or new **Suggestion** issue|Short; links to sources.|
+|Source inventory|Same issue or project description|URLs and doc paths only; no full copies.|
+|Assumption log|Intake summary or open-questions seed|Each assumption tagged `unverified`.|
+
+**Gate:** Do not create committed projects or **Todo** issues. Proceed when the agent can name what is known vs assumed.
+
+---
+
+### Phase 2 — Initiative/project selection or suggestion
+**Goal:** Place the work under the right initiative and project—or propose creating them.
+
+**Actions:**
+
+- Match an existing initiative/project using product name, repo remote, or user direction.
+- If none fits, propose a **Suggestion** initiative and/or **Suggestion** project with owner, lead, and Planning status.
+- Do not archive or replace live template projects; follow `create-planner-project` rules for real vs template projects.
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|
+|---|---|
+|Initiative link (existing or proposed)|Linear initiative|
+|Project link (existing or proposed)|Linear project in **Planning**, issues in **Suggestion**|
+|Placement note|Project description or status update explaining why this project was chosen or suggested|
+
+**Gate:** Human confirms initiative and project before phase 5 creates a full issue set from `planner-project-structure.md`.
+
+---
+
+### Phase 3 — Planning document selection and placement
+**Goal:** Decide which planning documents are needed and where each canonical copy lives.
+
+**Actions:**
+
+- Read filled or template **documentation placement rules** when they exist; otherwise use `documentation-placement-rules-template.md` defaults.
+- Read the **Planner guide** in `plugins/project-docs/README.md` for document chain order.
+- Build a document plan: which templates apply, primary home (Linear document vs repo `documents/`), and `related:` links.
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|
+|---|---|
+|Document plan table|Linear project document or **Suggestion** issue|
+|Per-doc placement decisions|Document plan; references placement rules section 3|
+
+**Gate:** No drafting of versioned repo docs until placement is agreed when the repo already exists.
+
+---
+
+### Phase 4 — Decision, risk, and open-question routing
+**Goal:** Route unresolved product and technical uncertainty to the right artifact—not into hidden issue descriptions.
+
+**Actions:**
+
+|If the item is...|Route to...|Skill / template|
+|---|---|---|
+|A choice that changes scope, behavior, cost, or future options|**Decision record** (draft)|`project-docs` → `decision-record-template.md`|
+|A threat to delivery, quality, cost, or operations|**Risk register** entry|Planner issue “Create risk register” or project Linear doc|
+|An unanswered question blocking or shaping work|**Open questions log**|Planner issue “Create open questions log”; project brief § Open questions for brief-level items|
+|Evidence needing a source trail|**Research brief**|`research-brief-template.md`|
+|External system the product depends on|**Platform dependency**|`platform-dependency-template.md`|
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|Linear state|
+|---|---|---|
+|Draft decision records|Linear document or repo `documents/` per placement rules|**Suggestion** until approved|
+|Risk register (seed)|Linear project doc or linked **Suggestion** issue|**Suggestion**|
+|Open questions log (seed)|Linear project doc or linked **Suggestion** issue|**Suggestion**|
+|Routing summary|Planning package index issue|Lists blockers vs non-blockers|
+
+**Gate:** Blocking open questions and unmitigated high-severity risks must be visible before phase 6. Do not mark planning “ready for execution” while blockers are hidden in prose.
+
+---
+
+### Phase 5 — Suggestion issue creation
+**Goal:** Break the planning package into reviewable Linear issues without committing execution work.
+
+**Actions:**
+
+- Create issues in **Suggestion** with clear titles, acceptance criteria, labels (`Planning`, `Documentation`, product label), and links to draft docs.
+- When using `planner-project-structure.md`, create the milestone and issue **titles** as suggestions; do not default them to **Todo**.
+- For doc-template skill work (for example “add skill for milestone plan template”), file **Suggestion** issues with `Agent Skill` and `Documentation` labels—not implementation todos.
+- Split large packages: one index **Suggestion** issue plus linked child suggestions.
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|
+|---|---|
+|Suggestion issue set|Linear project, all **Suggestion**|
+|Planning package index|One **Suggestion** issue linking brief, milestone plan, docs plan, risks, open questions|
+|Milestone outline|Linear milestones (optional) or milestone plan doc draft|
+
+**Gate:** Zero issues in **Todo**, **Ready**, or **In Progress** unless the user explicitly asked to promote specific items in this session.
+
+---
+
+### Phase 6 — Human verification
+**Goal:** A human confirms scope, ownership, priority, and sequencing before any committed work exists.
+
+**Human reviewer checks:**
+
+- [ ] Initiative and project are correct (or consciously created).
+- [ ] Document placement matches `documentation-placement-rules`.
+- [ ] Project brief (or equivalent) reflects agreed scope, non-goals, and success criteria.
+- [ ] Milestone plan matches intended sequencing.
+- [ ] Open questions: blockers resolved or explicitly accepted.
+- [ ] Risk register: owners and mitigations acceptable.
+- [ ] Decision records: approved or explicitly deferred with triggers.
+- [ ] Suggestion issues: priority, estimates, and labels make sense.
+- [ ] Nothing in the package assumes unverified facts as settled.
+
+**Agent actions during verification:**
+
+- Respond to review comments; update drafts; add missing links.
+- Do **not** promote issues or change project to **In Progress** without explicit human instruction.
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|
+|---|---|
+|Review notes|Linear comments on index issue or project|
+|Approved planning package|Status update: “Planning package verified by \<name\> on \<date\>”|
+
+---
+
+### Phase 7 — Conversion to committed work (post-review only)
+**Goal:** Turn verified planning into execution-ready Linear and repo artifacts.
+
+**Actions:**
+
+- Promote verified **Suggestion** issues to **Todo** or **Ready** in agreed priority order.
+- Move project from **Planning** to **In Progress** when the human signs off execution (aligns with Phase 4 gate in `planner-project-structure.md`).
+- Create **implementation brief** and **first execution backlog** only for items approved in phase 6:
+  - **Implementation brief:** use `project` → `task-spec` templates for a single bounded task; link feature spec / technical design.
+  - **First execution backlog:** ordered **Todo** issues derived from milestone plan and foundation phase; no new scope without a new suggestion cycle.
+
+**Produces:**
+
+|Output|Surface|State|
+|---|---|---|
+|Committed issues|Linear|**Todo** / **Ready**|
+|Implementation briefs|Issue bodies or repo docs per placement rules|**Todo**-linked|
+|First execution backlog|Linear issues under project|**Todo**|
+|Updated project brief / milestone plan|Canonical doc surface|**Approved** / Active|
+
+**Gate:** `pickup-work` and coding agents should only pick issues that passed phase 6–7.
+
+---
+
+## Planning artifact map
+Maps acceptance-criteria artifacts to templates, phases, and surfaces.
+
+|Artifact|Primary template / skill|Created in phase|Canonical surface (default)|Before human gate|
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+|**Project brief**|`project-brief-template.md` / `project-docs`|3–4|Linear project document; repo `documents/project-brief.md` when versioned|Draft; linked from **Suggestion** issues|
+|**Milestone plan**|`planner-project-structure.md` milestones + project doc|3–5|Linear project milestones + narrative doc|Outline only; issues stay **Suggestion**|
+|**Implementation brief**|`task-spec` → implementation brief section|7 only|Linear issue body or repo doc|Not created in phases 1–6|
+|**First execution backlog**|Derived from milestone plan + Phase 3 foundation issues|7|Linear **Todo** issues|Does not exist until phase 7|
+|**Open questions**|Brief §9 + open questions log issue|4|Linear project doc + index issue|**Suggestion** / draft|
+|**Risk register**|Planner “Create risk register” + project doc|4|Linear project doc|**Suggestion** / draft|
+|**Decision records**|`decision-record-template.md`|4|Repo or Linear per placement rules|**Suggestion** / In review|
+
+Supporting documents (customer profile, feature spec, technical design, testing strategy, release readiness) follow the same pattern: draft during phases 3–5, link from the planning package index, promote to **Approved** only after phase 6.
+
+---
+
+## Skill and entrypoint routing
+|Task|Use skill|Must follow suggestion-first?|
+|---|---|---|
+|Zero-to-planning package from rough idea|**agent-planning-workflow**|Yes|
+|Write or edit one planning document|**project-docs**|Yes for new docs; edits to approved docs need human intent|
+|Create Linear project skeleton from structure|**create-planner-project**|Yes — override default **Todo** with **Suggestion**|
+|Pick up coding work|**pickup-work**|No — only after phase 7|
+|Bounded task implementation brief|**task-spec**|After phase 7 for new execution|
+|Add or change templates in this repo|**create-doc-template**|Separate maintenance path; output is still reviewed via PR|
+
+---
+
+## Agent prohibitions
+- Do not move issues to **Todo**, **Ready**, or **In Progress** during phases 1–5.
+- Do not assign issues to a cycle by default.
+- Do not create implementation or “build feature X” issues during planning intake.
+- Do not duplicate canonical docs; link them.
+- Do not treat template example product names or issue IDs as real work.
+- Do not close the planning package with blocking open questions unlisted.
+
+---
+
+## Validation: ST-695 without scope duplication
+**ST-704** defines *how* planning agents work (this document).
+
+**ST-695** (and similar issues) define *what* to build next—for example a specific doc-template skill, template file, or agent entrypoint.
+
+Applying this workflow to ST-695:
+
+1. **Phases 1–2:** Intake names the template or skill ST-695 targets; suggest or attach the correct initiative/project under **Suggestion**.
+2. **Phase 3:** Document plan names only the templates ST-695 touches; other templates stay out of scope.
+3. **Phase 4:** Open questions and risks for ST-695 stay in the log—not buried in implementation notes.
+4. **Phase 5:** File ST-695 (and any split children) as **Suggestion** issues with acceptance criteria; do not create parallel **Todo** implementation issues for the same scope.
+5. **Phase 6:** Human verifies skill boundaries, labels, and placement rules alignment.
+6. **Phase 7:** After approval, promote ST-695 to **Todo** and optionally add an implementation brief; execution is ST-695’s job, not ST-704’s.
+
+ST-704 does not implement ST-695; it ensures ST-695 is not started as committed work before review.
+
